Name Rascal/Expressions/Values/Map/NotEqual

Synopsis Not equal operator on map values.
Syntax Exp1 != Exp2
Types
Exp1 Exp2 Exp1 != Exp2
map[TK1,TV2] map[TK2, TV2] bool
Description Yields true if both arguments contain different key/value pairs, and false otherwise.
Examples 
rascal>("apple": 1, "pear": 2) != ("apple": 1, "banana": 3);
bool: true
rascal>("apple": 1, "pear": 2) != ("pear": 2, "apple": 1);
bool: false
